WEBVTT

00:07.608 --> 00:10.144
Previously on "Billions"...

00:10.144 --> 00:12.580
When did it become a crime
to succeed in this country?

00:12.580 --> 00:14.382
[Bobby] Everyone has access
to the information.

00:14.382 --> 00:16.083
We just know
how to analyze it better.

00:16.083 --> 00:19.387
Suspect trading pattern
on Pepsum Pharmaceuticals.

00:19.387 --> 00:20.688
They had
inside information.

00:20.688 --> 00:22.456
You must get pings like that
every day.

00:22.456 --> 00:23.691
It's bigger than that.

00:23.691 --> 00:26.427
[Spyros] All three firms
have links to Bobby Axelrod.

00:26.427 --> 00:27.561
This would be a big one.

00:27.561 --> 00:31.031
But a good matador doesn't try
to kill a fresh bull.

00:31.031 --> 00:33.768
You wait until he's been stuck
a few times.

00:33.768 --> 00:35.803
Why aren't you prosecuting
the investment banks

00:35.803 --> 00:38.105
and hedge funds
for insider trading?

00:38.105 --> 00:40.541
Go ask the 81 convicted felons
of financial crimes

00:40.541 --> 00:42.243
currently serving time.

00:42.243 --> 00:44.245
But you have a very specific
conflict of interest

00:44.245 --> 00:45.179
right in your own home.

00:45.179 --> 00:47.281
Your value to the firm
is absolute.

00:47.281 --> 00:49.517
I've been working there
since before we were married

00:49.517 --> 00:51.185
and long before
you were in office.

00:51.185 --> 00:52.453
I work
for the public good.

00:52.453 --> 00:54.755
No, you work for the good
of Chuck Rhoades.

00:54.755 --> 00:57.057
Maybe sometimes
they intersect.

00:57.057 --> 00:58.492
You know the Norton place
out at the beach?

00:58.492 --> 00:59.593
[Sacker] I just heard

00:59.593 --> 01:00.761
Bobby Axelrod
is trying to buy it.

01:00.761 --> 01:02.329
[Bryan] How much?
[Sacker] $83 million.

01:02.329 --> 01:04.432
People hate guys
who buy things like that.

01:04.432 --> 01:07.067
[Hall] You said there was only
one thing you were afraid of --

01:07.067 --> 01:09.069
guys in windbreakers
walking in your office

01:09.069 --> 01:11.272
saying, "Step away
from the computer."

01:11.272 --> 01:13.507
And you told me you'd make sure
it wouldn't happen.

01:13.507 --> 01:14.542
So let me make sure.

01:14.542 --> 01:15.576
[Bobby] Steven Birch?

01:15.576 --> 01:16.644
[Hall]
It's either him or you.

01:16.644 --> 01:17.611
Piedmont Capital.

01:17.611 --> 01:19.113
Yeah.

01:19.113 --> 01:21.348
That swap deal he did
on Arcadian Railroad --

01:21.348 --> 01:23.417
Do an autopsy on the deal,

01:23.417 --> 01:25.519
you'll find yourself
a Pulitzer in the carcass.

01:27.121 --> 01:28.789
Front fucking page
of the Post.

01:29.857 --> 01:31.225
[Bryan] It's like
he's daring you.

01:31.225 --> 01:32.860
[Hall]
There's movement.

01:32.860 --> 01:35.663
It's likely they've opened
a case file on you.

01:35.663 --> 01:37.164
You know what?

01:37.164 --> 01:38.265
I'm ready.

