29:40.980 --> 29:42.948
Uh...

29:42.948 --> 29:44.817
you know what?

29:44.817 --> 29:46.051
Here's the $20

29:46.051 --> 29:48.220
for whatever the guy in
the blue shirt back there wants.

29:48.220 --> 29:50.055
[man] I got you.
Okay, thank you.

29:50.055 --> 29:51.824
[Chuck] Okay, guys, let's go.
Come on.

29:51.824 --> 29:54.193
Now, you guys remember
when we threw Grandpa

29:54.193 --> 29:55.528
a surprise party
for his birthday

29:55.528 --> 29:57.196
and we all
had to keep the secret?

29:57.196 --> 29:58.330
Yeah.

29:58.330 --> 30:00.099
Okay. Why do we
have to keep the secret?

30:00.099 --> 30:01.433
To make Grandpa happy.

30:01.433 --> 30:03.369
Right.
So this is like that, okay?

30:03.369 --> 30:05.137
We don't tell anyone
about the doughnuts

30:05.137 --> 30:06.972
to make Mommy  happy.

30:06.972 --> 30:07.873
Okay?

30:08.941 --> 30:09.975
[Kroll] Rhoades!

30:09.975 --> 30:13.179
Don't you walk away
before you meet my kids.

30:14.280 --> 30:17.349
Mr. Kroll,
we are in a public place...

30:17.349 --> 30:19.885
with, uh, as you say,
our children.

30:19.885 --> 30:22.888
Uh, why don't you guys go sit
on the bench over there, okay?

30:22.888 --> 30:24.557
Take your sister
over there.

30:25.558 --> 30:29.995
I-I don't need
your, um...kindness now.

30:29.995 --> 30:32.097
I-I needed it
at sentencing.

30:35.167 --> 30:38.504
This is
Margo and Stevie.

30:39.438 --> 30:40.839
Hello.

30:40.839 --> 30:43.042
I kept them out of school today
so we could be together

30:43.042 --> 30:44.944
because I go to prison
tomorrow.

30:46.345 --> 30:48.080
How do you
live with yourself?

30:48.080 --> 30:49.481
How?

30:49.481 --> 30:50.616
Yeah.

30:51.984 --> 30:53.219
I think long and hard

30:53.219 --> 30:57.523
before any prosecution
in my office goes forward.

30:57.523 --> 31:01.160
And I'm proudest of the cases
I choose not  to prosecute.

31:01.160 --> 31:04.597
But when I go forward,
it's full guns.

31:04.597 --> 31:07.166
I made
one goddamn mistake.

31:07.166 --> 31:09.635
And who got hurt?

31:09.635 --> 31:10.569
No one.

31:10.569 --> 31:11.637
[Kroll]
You could have let it go.

31:11.637 --> 31:12.938
You committed mail fraud.

31:12.938 --> 31:16.275
And you knew
that my wife had died...

31:16.275 --> 31:18.244
suddenly...

31:18.244 --> 31:20.446
and that I was
desperate and lost.

31:20.446 --> 31:21.880
Y-You read the articles.

31:21.880 --> 31:23.315
You -- You got letters
from 100 people

31:23.315 --> 31:25.884
who vouched for the man
that I was and would be again.

31:27.386 --> 31:30.489
I'm what those kids
have left.

31:30.489 --> 31:34.560
And they won't have me again
for four years.

31:36.161 --> 31:37.930
Have a nice stroll
with yours.

31:37.930 --> 31:39.565
And take your fucking $20

31:39.565 --> 31:42.568
or just...leave it here
for the birds to pick at.

31:45.170 --> 31:46.405
[Kroll] Let's go, kids.

31:46.405 --> 31:48.307
Daddy's done
with this asshole.

31:53.445 --> 31:55.014
[Butch]
You wanted to see me?

31:55.014 --> 31:56.382
Hey.

31:57.916 --> 31:59.685
I want to give you a short

31:59.685 --> 32:02.421
that you're not gonna bail on
too quick.

32:02.421 --> 32:03.922
Do you know Cross-Co.?

32:03.922 --> 32:05.624
Cross-Co. Trucking.
I've been tracking it.

32:05.624 --> 32:08.427
Mid-size firm,
has a big distribution contract

32:08.427 --> 32:10.462
with that bakery company
YumTime.

32:10.462 --> 32:12.231
Been holding 50.

32:12.231 --> 32:14.433
Fundamentals are solid.

32:14.433 --> 32:16.402
I don't see
the short play.

32:16.402 --> 32:19.171
I don't need you to see it.
I need you to do  it.

32:19.171 --> 32:21.573
We'll get 50 on the tape.
We'll size up later.

32:23.642 --> 32:27.079
[Bobby] You got
a fucking problem with this?

32:27.079 --> 32:28.047
No.

32:34.320 --> 32:35.487
[sighs]

32:35.487 --> 32:37.156
You plug
that investor leakage?

32:37.156 --> 32:39.124
I thought I'd done
exactly that,

32:39.124 --> 32:41.527
but I haven't been able
to get Garth Sykes on the phone.

32:42.428 --> 32:44.296
He bails, it hurts us.

32:44.296 --> 32:46.031
Yeah. I tried.

32:46.031 --> 32:48.434
But I think I need you
to show face with this guy.

32:48.434 --> 32:50.135
You got this.

32:50.135 --> 32:51.403
That's why I have you.

32:51.403 --> 32:52.671
[keyboard clacking]

32:52.671 --> 32:55.574
[birds chirping]

32:55.574 --> 32:57.676
That fucker thinks that
if you  come running over here,

32:57.676 --> 33:00.546
I'm gonna forget he fired me
in front of everyone I know?

33:00.546 --> 33:02.247
Who knows
what he thinks?

33:02.247 --> 33:04.149
One minute,
you're his most trusted advisor,

33:04.149 --> 33:06.385
the next,
you're on the outside.

33:06.385 --> 33:08.153
I'm here because...

33:08.153 --> 33:09.722
I think you might
make it worse for yourself,

33:09.722 --> 33:11.190
and I don't want
to see that.

33:11.190 --> 33:13.425
The money I made him...

33:13.425 --> 33:15.260
He treated me
like a lowlife.

33:15.260 --> 33:17.429
And that's a trigger
for you.

33:17.429 --> 33:19.331
Everyone laughing at me
growing up.

33:19.331 --> 33:21.066
The dyslexia.

33:21.066 --> 33:22.468
Even the teachers.

33:22.468 --> 33:24.169
I sent
every one of those pricks

33:24.169 --> 33:26.538
a photo of my first
million-dollar bonus check.

33:26.538 --> 33:30.075
That made you feel really good
for about 24 hours,

33:30.075 --> 33:31.310
and then
you hated yourself

33:31.310 --> 33:33.645
for letting them know
they ever got to you.

33:33.645 --> 33:34.747
Kind of.

33:34.747 --> 33:37.149
Sometimes.

33:37.149 --> 33:39.118
This is different.

33:39.118 --> 33:41.553
I know plenty about
how Axe Capital works --

33:41.553 --> 33:43.155
the dirty edge...

33:43.155 --> 33:45.491
the proprietary trading
techniques.

33:45.491 --> 33:47.092
I know how
the secret sauce is made.

33:47.092 --> 33:47.693
Yeah.

33:47.693 --> 33:49.027
I'm sure
you could put out

33:49.027 --> 33:50.396
a Schott's Miscellany
about the place.

33:50.396 --> 33:51.663
Schott's?

33:51.663 --> 33:54.733
It's like a Farmers' Almanac
for non-farm stuff.

33:54.733 --> 33:57.603
Then, yeah, I could put out
a couple of volumes

33:57.603 --> 33:59.271
of Schott's Miscellany
about the place.

33:59.271 --> 34:01.673
You just need to ask yourself
one question first --

34:01.673 --> 34:04.343
are you rich enough
to never get another job?

34:08.580 --> 34:10.783
I did work
for that man.

34:10.783 --> 34:12.551
Bribed an oil company C.F.O.
for him --

34:12.551 --> 34:14.052
Stop talking.

34:14.052 --> 34:16.054
We're not in session.
That's not privileged.

34:16.054 --> 34:19.625
Point is, I got
all muddied up for him.

34:19.625 --> 34:22.461
Hard not to rub it
on his clean, white shirt now.

34:27.065 --> 34:29.101
Remember Warren Jaffin,
the analyst?

34:30.269 --> 34:31.537
Yeah.

34:31.537 --> 34:33.205
Bright guy?

34:33.205 --> 34:34.339
That kid was sharp.

34:34.339 --> 34:36.308
Employable?

34:36.308 --> 34:37.409
Real  sharp, yeah.

34:37.409 --> 34:40.212
Then he balked at his bonus
one year and got popped.

34:40.212 --> 34:43.148
He got another job right away
at a huge bank --

34:43.148 --> 34:45.217
$3 million a year,
guaranteed.

34:45.217 --> 34:46.385
Only,
word got back to Axe

34:46.385 --> 34:48.587
that Warren had badmouthed him
in the interview --

34:48.587 --> 34:50.789
said Axe
wasn't generous with him.

34:50.789 --> 34:54.126
So Axe called
the head of the bank,

34:54.126 --> 34:57.696
asked him to pull the offer
that day, which the guy did.

34:59.565 --> 35:01.500
Can you imagine...

35:01.500 --> 35:04.269
how humiliating that was
for Warren?

35:04.269 --> 35:06.171
Probably told his whole family,
all his friends

35:06.171 --> 35:07.473
that he was back.

35:07.473 --> 35:09.308
But Axe
didn't leave it there.

35:09.308 --> 35:11.410
He called
the president or chairman

35:11.410 --> 35:14.513
of every prime broker, bank,
and fund in the industry

35:14.513 --> 35:15.781
and had him blackballed.

35:15.781 --> 35:17.549
Put it out
over the loudspeaker,

35:17.549 --> 35:19.518
direct from
the principal's office --

35:19.518 --> 35:23.188
"If you hire Warren Jaffin,
you are my enemy."

35:24.490 --> 35:27.860
[Wendy] Do you know
what Warren does now?

35:29.595 --> 35:31.263
He's got a blog.

35:34.299 --> 35:37.269
You've built a real life
for yourself, Victor --

35:37.269 --> 35:38.637
a long way from Queens.

35:38.637 --> 35:39.872
[sighs]

35:39.872 --> 35:42.140
If Axe is certain
you'll act like a gentleman,

35:42.140 --> 35:44.610
he will make sure
to take care of you.

35:46.278 --> 35:47.746
You were the one
that always told me

35:47.746 --> 35:49.248
to stand up for myself.

35:49.248 --> 35:52.618
When you can win, yes.

35:52.618 --> 35:56.421
The only way you can win now
is by letting it go.

36:02.461 --> 36:05.764
You know,
I have to confess to something.

36:05.764 --> 36:07.165
Okay.

36:07.165 --> 36:08.534
[sighs]
You're not gonna like it.

36:08.534 --> 36:10.235
Fire away.

36:10.235 --> 36:13.272
I took the kids
for doughnuts.

36:13.272 --> 36:15.374
I know.

36:15.374 --> 36:16.808
Kevin told me.

36:18.544 --> 36:19.545
Good.

36:19.545 --> 36:20.812
Oh.

36:20.812 --> 36:22.414
You're glad he cracked?

36:22.414 --> 36:25.450
No, I never want them
to keep secrets from you.

36:25.450 --> 36:27.953
They're gonna keep them from me
their entire teenage years.

36:27.953 --> 36:29.187
They should at least know

36:29.187 --> 36:31.557
that they always can confide
in you.

36:31.557 --> 36:36.228
[Chuck] And among your many
gifts, that is a great one.

36:36.228 --> 36:39.765
Everyone feels like
you're always on their side.

36:39.765 --> 36:42.968
Well, I try  to be,
or at least...

36:42.968 --> 36:45.337
understand
where they're coming from.

36:45.337 --> 36:46.939
[Chuck] That's
the wonderful part of your job.

36:46.939 --> 36:49.508
You get to employ
your empathy.

36:50.676 --> 36:55.614
I have to be a real prick
sometimes, you know?

36:55.614 --> 36:56.882
At work.

36:56.882 --> 36:59.217
Yeah.

36:59.217 --> 37:02.588
Sometimes, we all  do things
we're not proud of at work.

37:02.588 --> 37:04.556
[Chuck]
Well, this is different.

37:05.724 --> 37:08.226
When I was in the park
with the kids,

37:08.226 --> 37:10.662
there was this guy
who...

37:11.830 --> 37:15.334
Specifics don't matter.

37:15.334 --> 37:16.668
What does is,

37:16.668 --> 37:20.405
that every once in a while,
there's this thing we say --

37:20.405 --> 37:21.807
"I am never so proud

37:21.807 --> 37:25.911
as when I choose
not  to prosecute a case."

37:25.911 --> 37:29.381
And that's true --
in theory.

37:29.381 --> 37:33.518
But once in a while, I wish
that I could just be more...

37:35.821 --> 37:37.823
...human.

37:40.525 --> 37:42.527
But I haven't figured out
how to do that

37:42.527 --> 37:45.731
and  my job
at the same time.

37:45.731 --> 37:46.832
You know?

37:46.832 --> 37:50.469
Being 100% good
at your job...

37:52.638 --> 37:55.507
...and 100% good...

37:57.409 --> 37:58.744
...if you figure
that one out,

37:58.744 --> 38:00.646
let's both quit
and write that book.

