38:12.991 --> 38:14.860
It's a luxury to relax
every once in a while,

38:14.860 --> 38:16.328
isn't it, Garth?

38:16.328 --> 38:18.897
I remember this place --
fondly.

38:18.897 --> 38:20.832
Look, the stability
of this firm

38:20.832 --> 38:22.501
has never been in question.

38:22.501 --> 38:25.904
I need to look into
Axelrod's eyes, hear him  say it.

38:25.904 --> 38:27.939
Yeah, he will.

38:27.939 --> 38:29.775
I just wanted
to hear you first.

38:29.775 --> 38:32.444
I may be from Kentucky,
but I'm no rube.

38:32.444 --> 38:33.645
I don't bet on long shots

38:33.645 --> 38:36.682
when it comes to investing
the pensions of my members.

38:36.682 --> 38:39.918
That's why they trust me
with their $5 billion.

38:39.918 --> 38:43.355
I get nervous, I see someone
like Axelrod running around

38:43.355 --> 38:46.058
spending his money
like he's a goddamn rap singer.

38:46.058 --> 38:48.894
Emcee.
Like a rap emcee.

38:48.894 --> 38:51.563
No, some of 'em sing now.
My kids showed me.

38:51.563 --> 38:54.399
Snoop and Kid Rock both.

38:54.399 --> 38:58.336
You're right --
you are no rube.

38:58.336 --> 39:00.839
But Bobby Axelrod isn't,
either.

39:00.839 --> 39:03.842
We've crushed the S&P
seven years running,

39:03.842 --> 39:07.412
which means
you  have crushed the S&P.

39:07.412 --> 39:09.014
[woman]
You turn over now.

39:09.014 --> 39:10.449
[groans]

39:10.449 --> 39:13.719
Everyone  beats it --
till they don't.

39:13.719 --> 39:16.888
When I can I see Axe,
talk to him about it?

39:16.888 --> 39:19.558
You don't want
to rush off now,  do you?

39:19.558 --> 39:20.926
[both moan]

